result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Ryan Andre Burdette in court.  Attorney Jason A Findling in court for Ryan Andre Burdette.  Prosecuting attorney Michelle A. Grasso in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State:  West Allis Police Officer Tyler Gibson  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  
Defense is requesting final pretrial and jury trial dates. Case is adjourned to 11-10-22 at 8:30 for final pretrial and 12-14-22 at 8:30 am for jury trial.
Final pre-trial scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Jury trial scheduled for December 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.
Court ordered defendant to have any any alcohol or drugs or weapons.

DEFENDANT HAS TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED WITHIN 24 HOURS.

Defendant Ryan Andre Burdette in court with attorney Jason A Findling.  Michelle A. Grasso appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Havas, Branch 10.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 22, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered no contact with ARL.
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
